Package com.coremedia.iso.boxes.odf

Class Summary
MutableDrmInformationBox A mutable DRM information box may appear in both DCF and PDCF.
OmaDrmCommonHeadersBox The Common Headers Box defines a structure for required headers in a DCF file.
OmaDrmContainerBox The OMA DRM Container box is the container for a single content object in a OMA DCF file.
OmaDrmContentIdBox The ContentID box (‘ccid’) contains the unique identifier for the Content Object the metadata are associated with.
OmaDrmContentObjectBox  
OmaDrmCoverUriBox A vodafone specific box.
OmaDrmDiscreteHeadersBox The Discrete Media headers box includes fields specific to the DCF format and the OmaDrmCommonHeadersBox, followed by an optional UserDataBox.
OmaDrmGroupIdBox The GroupId value identifies this DCF as part of a group of DCFs whose Rights can be defined in a common group Rights Object instead of (or in addition to) in separate content-specific Rights Objects.
OmaDrmIconUriBox The IconURI box contains a URI where an appropriate icon for this content may be retrieved from.
OmaDrmInfoUrlBox The InfoURL box ('infu') contains a URL where additional information can be found regarding the Content Object.
OmaDrmKeyManagenentSystemBox Signals OMA Key Management in a PDCF file.
OmaDrmLyricsUriBox A box in the UserDataBox containing information about the lyric location.
OmaDrmRightsObjectBox The rights object box MAY be used to insert a Protected Rights Object, defined in [DRM-v2] section 5.3.7, i nto a DCF or PDCF.
OmaDrmTransactionTrackingBox The OMA DRM Transaction Tracking Box enables transaction tracking as defined OMA DRM 2.0.
